<br>
I say this because Zemm and company are drakes.  Therefore they have a liking to their own kind.  Many creatures throughout everquest exhibit such behavior when they are not on any factions.<br>
<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
Some newbies are fighting a rattlesnake in WC.  A giant spider wanders on by, says &quot;Howdy do!&quot; to the group killing the snake, and goes about his business.<br>
<br>
Same group then fights a spider, however, buddy-spider comes along and sees them killing his friend!  So he rushes in to rescue his pal.<br>
<br>
Spiders don't care about snakes, snakes don't care about spiders.  Spiders care about spiders and will help their buddies when they are in danger.<br>
<br>
Now, while this may not entirely be approriate to the situation, let's say we have Bob the Drake, and he's chillin' about in the Halls of Testing, drinking his margarita and suddenly some monk tags him in the head!  Bob then makes much haste for said monk, and finds himself in the middle of a group of angry individuals, all set on killing him.  Bob has no desire to go down without a fight, so he is bounced around a few times, running near the door, shouting &quot;Help, help!  I'm a drake getting beat up by this gang of ruffians!&quot;<br>
<br>
Zemm, being the upstanding member of the drake community says, &quot;C'mon boys, there's one of our own in trouble, let's help him out!&quot;<br>
<br>
And in comes Zemm and his pals, coming to punch everyone in the face who is hurting one of his people.<br>
<br>
This is pure speculation and untested, but follows behaviors of mechanics that I've seen before with unfactioned mobs of like types that are unaggro, and may not apply to this situation.<br>
<br>
